# Agent Registry & Reseed Conventions

## Labels in Agent UI

Do **not** use parenthetical text in labels for agent-related forms (e.g. `(optional)`, `(A2A)` in field labels).

- **Prefer:** Plain labels — e.g. "Name override", "Description", "Description override"
- **Avoid:** "Name override (optional)", "Description (optional)"

Use placeholders or helper text to indicate optionality instead of `(optional)` in the label.

## Reseed / Agent Bootstrap

When adding or changing agent seed data, forms, or agent list UI:

- Keep agent form labels free of parentheticals
- **Agent names in seed data**: Do not use parentheticals in agent names (e.g. no "(Resolution)", "(Lead)").
  Use plain suffixes: " Lead", " Support", " Resolution" etc. so names read like "Strategy Data Quality Resolution Agent".
- Use A2A-aligned naming (e.g. "Service URL" not "A2A URL") per project convention
- **Full reseed (db:full-reset-pg / seed-postgres.js)**: After inserting agents, backfill `created_at` and `updated_at` with random dates in the last 6 months so the Registered column and "last updated" sort show varied dates.
